.TH "pwm_omap_dmtimer_config" 9 "pwm_omap_dmtimer_config" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pwm_omap_dmtimer_config \- Update the configuration of pwm omap dm timer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pwm_omap_dmtimer_config
.BI "(struct pwm_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "struct pwm_device *pwm "  ","
.BI "int duty_ns "  ","
.BI "int period_ns "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
Pointer to PWM controller
.IP "pwm" 12
Pointer to PWM channel
.IP "duty_ns" 12
New duty cycle in nano seconds
.IP "period_ns" 12
New period in nano seconds
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return 0 if successfully changed the period/duty_cycle else appropriate
error.
